The President of the United States issued a statement expressing his support for the peace agreement between Colombia and the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC). He commended the Colombian leaders and citizens who worked towards this milestone and thanked President Juan Manuel Santos, the government of Cuba, Norway, and the United States' Special Envoy for their contributions to the peace process. The President acknowledged that achieving a just and lasting peace will require further work, but pledged the support of the United States in this endeavor. He also recognized the transformation that Colombia has undergone and expressed pride in standing with the Colombian people as they strive for peace and prosperity.